 \"the competitive formbetter\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ironically, she may have also made herself the world's most famous hip-hop artist for that moment, a travesty that hurts real hip-hop artists and furthers damaging stereotypes of Black art.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that moment\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"a travesty\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 766}, {\"ngram\": \"real hip-hop artists\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 798}, {\"ngram\": \"damaging stereotypes\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"Black art\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hip-hop culture, which includes among its original elements breaking, graffiti art, DJing and emceeing (rapping), has spread worldwide since its origins among Black artists in the early 1970s.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.9999986063367649, \"rank\": 1.3936649618113444e-06, \"text\": \"DJing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hip-hop culture\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"its original elements\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"graffiti art\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"emceeing (rapping\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"its origins\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1000}, {\"ngram\": \"Black artists\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then it has garnered bothpopular acclaim and academic interest, as well ascriticism heavily influenced by racism, both hidden and overt.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bothpopular acclaim\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"academic interest\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1109}, {\"ngram\": \"ascriticism\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"racism\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The excessive attention paid to Gunn's poor performance is tinged withanti-Blackness-the systematic disdain for Black people and cultural forms-that has beenlikened to minstrelsy.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.96451616515103, \"rank\": 0.01927309492072504, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The excessive attention\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"the systematic disdain\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"Black people\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural forms\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1328}, {\"ngram\": \"minstrelsy\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1363}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to upstaging the Olympic competition and making a mockery of hip-hop culture, viral news of the debacle has further fueled this anti-Blackness that has, for decades, been weaponized against hip-hop and other Black art.\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic competition\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop culture\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"viral news\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"the debacle\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1480}, {\"ngram\": \"this anti\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1509}, {\"ngram\": \"Blackness\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"other Black art\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are enjoying this article, consider supporting our award-winning journalism bysubscribing.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1629}, {\"ngram\": \"our award-winning journalism\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By purchasing a subscription you are helping to ensure the future of impactful stories about the discoveries and ideas shaping our world today.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a subscription\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"impactful stories\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the discoveries\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1803}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"our world\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I know how this happens because I have experienced it personally.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been a lifelong hip-hop artist.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lifelong hip-hop artist\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2017 I watchednews of my doctoral dissertation, a rap album titledOwning My Masters: The Rhetorics of Rhymes & Revolutions,go viral.\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my doctoral dissertation\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"a rap album\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"My Masters\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"The Rhetorics\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"Rhymes\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2056}, {\"ngram\": \"Revolutions\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of this attention felt like sincere interest in the work, but some of it proliferated among people who disdained both Black art and Black scholarship.\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this attention\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"sincere interest\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"both Black art\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"Black scholarship\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asecond wave of such attentioncame from the same sort of observers when I was hired to an academic position focused on hip-hop at the University of Virginia in 2017.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2402, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Asecond wave\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2249}, {\"ngram\": \"such attentioncame\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2271}, {\"ngram\": \"the same sort\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"observers\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"an academic position\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2363}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"Virginia\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Given the ubiquity of hip-hop globally, it's remarkable that it took until that time for a university to establish what was then my role as an assistant professor of hip-hop.\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ubiquity\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2422}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2433}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"a university\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2505}, {\"ngram\": \"my role\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"an assistant professor\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2566}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am now an associate professor of the subject.)\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an associate professor\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the subject\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What I have learned is that, unfortunately, racist culturalassumptions about hip-hoplead audiences to dismiss its art and scholarship.\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hip-hoplead audiences\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"its art\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2746}, {\"ngram\": \"scholarship\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Misguided assumptions about rap and rappers lead audiences to believe that hip-hop and academic achievements are at odds with one another.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2902, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Misguided assumptions\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"rap\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"rappers\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"audiences\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2822}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2846}, {\"ngram\": \"academic achievements\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2872}, {\"ngram\": \"odds\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of this, the novelty of someone earning a Ph.D. by rapping is hard to disentangle from long-held negative stereotypes.\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 3029, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the novelty\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2931}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 2942}, {\"ngram\": \"a Ph.D.\", \"from\": 2951, \"to\": 2958}, {\"ngram\": \"long-held negative stereotypes\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These stereotypes are fed by some narrating such occurrences as \\\"unlikely\\\" rather than a product of deliberate exclusion.\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These stereotypes\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"some narrating\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"such occurrences\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"a product\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"deliberate exclusion\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is alsothe history of Black culture and music being co-opted.\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"alsothe history\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"Black culture\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Institutions like universities and record companies colonize the music.\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3291, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Institutions\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3232}, {\"ngram\": \"universities\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"record companies\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3271}, {\"ngram\": \"the music\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3290}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their \\\"discovery\\\" and \\\"study\\\" become vehicles to confer expertise and make money through a process of whitewashing that removes control of the culture and its products from Black people.\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3478, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their \\\"discovery\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3308}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"study\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"vehicles\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3337}, {\"ngram\": \"expertise\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3357}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3372}, {\"ngram\": \"a process\", \"from\": 3381, \"to\": 3390}, {\"ngram\": \"whitewashing\", \"from\": 3394, \"to\": 3406}, {\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"the culture\", \"from\": 3431, \"to\": 3442}, {\"ngram\": \"its products\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3459}, {\"ngram\": \"Black people\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"William E. Ketchum III, writing forRolling Stoneabout the online school for lyricism,Pendulum Ink Academy, highlights a tension I feel: \\\"On one side, if academia is supposed to reflect what's going on in the real world, hip-hop should be a part of it.\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3490, \"end\": 3497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ketchum_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5339359563456937e-24, \"text\": \"Ketchum\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ketchum_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ketchum_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 3498, \"end\": 3501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_III\", \"score\": 0.9978491507199267, \"rank\": 0.0020935460940492705, \"text\": \"III\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_III\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_III\"}, {\"begin\": 3564, \"end\": 3572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pendulum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.559627279474025e-23, \"text\": \"Pendulum\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pendulum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pendulum\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"forRolling Stoneabout\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3532}, {\"ngram\": \"the online school\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3550}, {\"ngram\": \"lyricism\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3563}, {\"ngram\": \"a tension\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3606}, {\"ngram\": \"one side\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3627}, {\"ngram\": \"academia\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3640}, {\"ngram\": \"the real world\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3697}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3706}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 3717, \"to\": 3723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But on the other side, when these predominantly white spaces integrate hip-hop into what they are doing, it often loses the essence of what hip-hop is.\\\"\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3883, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3752}, {\"ngram\": \"these predominantly white spaces\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3791}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 3802, \"to\": 3809}, {\"ngram\": \"the essence\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3862}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 3878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gunn is also an academic whoreportedly studies breaking.\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3885, \"end\": 3889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.96451616515103, \"rank\": 0.01927309492072504, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an academic whoreportedly studies\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of the coverage of her foregrounds her academic credentials.\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 4007, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the coverage\", \"from\": 3950, \"to\": 3962}, {\"ngram\": \"her academic credentials\", \"from\": 3982, \"to\": 4006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This works to render her ability (or lack thereof) as novelty, giving detractors ammunition to leverage against hip-hopandacademia.\", \"from\": 4008, \"to\": 4139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her ability\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4040}, {\"ngram\": \"novelty\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4069}, {\"ngram\": \"detractors\", \"from\": 4078, \"to\": 4088}, {\"ngram\": \"ammunition\", \"from\": 4089, \"to\": 4099}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hopandacademia\", \"from\": 4120, \"to\": 4138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the widespread attention may open up potential future publishing opportunities andmedia appearancesfor her, it may unintentionally cast negative light on earnest, valuable scholarly explorations of hip-hop cultural forms.\", \"from\": 4140, \"to\": 4367, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the widespread attention\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4170}, {\"ngram\": \"potential future publishing opportunities andmedia\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4233}, {\"ngram\": \"negative light\", \"from\": 4282, \"to\": 4296}, {\"ngram\": \"earnest, valuable scholarly explorations\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4340}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop cultural forms\", \"from\": 4344, \"to\": 4366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Associations with the attention afforded scholars like her are why I expressly did not want to become a \\\"hip-hop scholar\\\" by earning a Ph.D.; I wanted to avoid the ways that the term seems to describe some academics who feel encouraged to unquestioningly colonize the culture and try to be its loudest and most visible authorities.\", \"from\": 4368, \"to\": 4699, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Associations\", \"from\": 4368, \"to\": 4380}, {\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4399}, {\"ngram\": \"scholars\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4417}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"hip-hop scholar\", \"from\": 4470, \"to\": 4488}, {\"ngram\": \"a Ph.D.\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4508}, {\"ngram\": \"the ways\", \"from\": 4528, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"the term\", \"from\": 4542, \"to\": 4550}, {\"ngram\": \"some academics\", \"from\": 4569, \"to\": 4583}, {\"ngram\": \"the culture\", \"from\": 4632, \"to\": 4643}, {\"ngram\": \"its loudest and most visible authorities\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Root's Noah McGee noted how some academicsexcused Gunn's performancewith language in which hip-hop artists-people like me-were considered objects of study, unthinking things, a perpetual problem.\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4755, \"end\": 4759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.96451616515103, \"rank\": 0.01927309492072504, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Root's Noah McGee\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\